sources.title: The Last of the Clintons (1935) HARRY CAREY
sources.description:
Stars: Harry Carey, Betty Mack, Del Gordon
Writer/Director: Harry Fraser

A cowboy infiltrates an outlaw gang to expose them, but after he's ordered to kidnap a young girl they find out his true identity!

Movie Class by PizzaFLIX: Harry Carey (1878â€“1947) began acting in 1910 to become one of Silent Film's earliest superstars and successfully transitioned into "talkies." He made 260 films and is best remembered as a cowboy. So much so, John Ford and John Wayne closed their iconic western THE SEARCHERS (1956) with a visual homage to Harry Carey.

metadata.Plot: Trigger Carson arrives to help Elkins' vigilante group round up a gang of rustlers. Posing as an outlaw, he and his sidekick Jed join up with the gang who are led by Luke Todd. When Elkins' daughter Edith reveals his identity, he needs Jed's help to let him and Edith escape. Then he heads back to finish the job.
metadata.Actors: Harry Carey, Betty Mack, Del Gordon
